<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy to Aid Pakistan's Development Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The government of Italy will
provide a soft loan of 30 billion liras (19.2 million US dollar)
to Pakistan for various development projects aimed at
strengthening small and medium sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The record of talks between the governments of Italy and
Pakistan concerning the loan was signed here today by Pietro
Rinaldi, Italian Ambassador to Pakistan, and Rashid Mahmood
Ansari, joint secretary of the Economic Affairs Division of the
Pakistani government.
</P>
<P>
Under the record of talks, enterprises such as automobiles
fittings, building materials, chemical industry, electronics,
energy saving, leather, mechanical engineering, pharmacy, printing
and packaging and textile will enjoy the loan.
</P>
<P>
This soft loan may also be utilized for co-financing World Bank
projects in the said sectors.
</P>
<P>
The Italian government also agreed to provide 3.2 billion liras
(2.0 million US dollars) in grants to finance the T.B. Control
Program in North West Frontier Province and the Post Graduate
study program of the National Excellence Center for Advanced
Molecular Biology in the University of Punjab.
</P>
<P>
The present agreement will serve as a new impetus to the
existing Pak-Italy economic cooperation, said official sources
while commenting on the signed record.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
