SARAJEVO -- The European Union (EU) and the Bosnian Croats
failed to reach an agreement Saturday during their negotiations on
ending the boycott of the Mostar city council.
</P>
<P>
ATHENS -- The entire fortune of former Greek prime minister
Andreas Papandreou will be inherited by his widow Dimitra Liani
under the terms of his will, local press reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
BUCHAREST -- Romanian President Ion Iliescu Sunday welcomed the
U.S. decision to grant his country the most-favored nation (MFN)
treatment which would improve the bilateral trade relations. 
