<HEADLINE> Cuba Wins Fourth Boxing Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Hector Vinent added one more
gold medal to Cuba's tally after defeating Okatay Urkal of
Germany in the 63.5kg class final.
</P>
<P>
So far Cuba has won four boxing gold medals at the Centennial
Olympic Games to justify that it is the powerhouse in amateur
boxing.
</P>
<P>
Vinent was stronger and faster in the bout and he floored
Urkal in the first round.
</P>
