<HEADLINE> Hosts Finally Win a Boxing Medal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Hosts the United States finally
won a boxing gold medal when David Reid scored a knock-out
victory over Alfredo Duvergel of Cuba in the 71kg class final.
</P>
<P>
The bout was full of drama as Alfredo dominated the first
round and forced Reid to his first count of eight.
</P>
<P>
But the American fought back in the second round and gained
an upper hand over his Cuban rival.
</P>
<P>
In the third round, the two boxers fastened their attacking
and with a fierce combination, Reid knocked down Alfredo to give
the United States the first boxing gold medal at the current
Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Ezmouhan Ibzaimov of Kazakhstan and Karim Tulaganov of
Uzbekistan finished a joint third for the bronze medal. 
</P>
