<DOCNO> XIE19960805.0033 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Croatia Beats Sweden to Win Men's Handball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Croatia defeated Sweden 27-26 in
a thrilling match between two European powerhouses in the gold
medal game of the men's handball tournament here today.
</P>
<P>
The victory brought the Croatians their first gold medal at the
26th Olympic Games, which close this evening.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish opened the score, but missed several following
shots, including a penalty shot. The Croatians scored six
consecutive goals to lead the Swedish 7-6 with 20 minutes into the
game.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish made a surge, but were only able to cut their
deficit to four goals. At the end of the first half, the Croatians
scored another goal, finishing with 16-11.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, the Croatians expanded their lead to 20-13
in the first 10 minutes. But the Swedish made a late game surge to
cut their deficit to one goal with three minutes to go. The
Croatians were within their striking distance.
</P>
<P>
In a tense atmosphere, the two teams traded goals. The
Croatians scored a goal to lead with 27-25 with 26 seconds left in
the game and the Swedish returned a goal before the end, missing
the gold medal by one goal.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today in the bronze medal game, Spain beat France 27-25
to win the third place in the men's handball tournament.
</P>
<P>
In the women's tournament, Denmark upset defending champion
South Korea Saturday to capture the gold medal. South Korea, a
two-time Olympic champion, received the silver. Hungary took the
bronze after triumphed over Norway in the bronze medal game. China
was the fifth after defeating the United States and Germany.
</P>
</TEXT>
