<HEADLINE> Boxer From Tonga Takes Silver Medal at Olympic Boxing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Paea Wolfgram of Tonga surprised
the boxing world by winning the silver medal of the over 91kg
category at the Olympics on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Wolfgram, who beat Duncan Dokiwari of Nigeria to book a berth
in Sunday's final, once took a lead of 2-1 in the first round.
</P>
<P>
But his opponent Vladimir Klichko of Ukraine fought steadily in
the following two rounds while Wolfgram seemed tired and had to
settle for the silver medal.
</P>
<P>
Klichko's victory gave Ukraine the only boxing gold at the
Centennial Olympics. Alexei Lezin of Russia shared the bronze
medal with Dokiwari. 
</P>
