<HEADLINE> 16 People Killed in Car Accident in Northern </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 4 (Xinhua) -- 16 people were killed in a
car accident which occured on Saturday at Daudi Division in
Arusha Region, Northern Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Arusha Police Commander Alfred Ntobi told reporters in Arusha
that the accident, which involved a lorry, was caused by
over-loading and speeding.
</P>
<P>
The lorry, which was travelling to Endabashi Market from Daudi
Division, was carrying businesspesons and ordinary travellers.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the lorry is being held by the police in
connection with the accident. 
</P>
