<HEADLINE> Turkish Speaker Leaves for Visit to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Speaker of the Turkish Grand
National Assembly Mustafa Kalemli left here this evening for a
one-week visit to China in a bid to further develop the existing
friendly ties between China and Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Kalemli said in a written statement at the Ankara Esenboga
Airport that he will meet with Chairman of the Standing Committee
of the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC) Qiao Shi, Prime
Minister Li Peng and Vice Chairman of the NPC Standing Committee
Tian Jiyun.
</P>
<P>
Turkish sources said that Kalemli has brought a message from
Turkish Prime Minister Necmettin Erbakan to Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
A seven-member delegation led by the Turkish speaker is paying
the visit to China at a time when the two countries are marking
the 25th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Turkey Wu Keming saw the Turkish
parliamentary delegation off at the airport. 
</P>
</TEXT>
