<HEADLINE> AL Condemns Israel's Decision to Lift Ban on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League today condemned the
Israeli government's decision to lift a ban on expansion of Jewish
settlements in the West Bank and Gaza Strip.
</P>
<P>
The 22-member league said in a statement that the decision is a
big obstacle to the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli cabinet voted unanimously Friday to lift the
building restrictions on construction of the Jewish settlements in
the Palestinian territories.
</P>
<P>
The restrictions were imposed by Israel's late Prime Minister
Yitzhak Rabin four years ago to pave the way for peace
negotiations with the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
The recent decision proves the Israeli government's intention
to Judaize and seize Palestinian lands, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The Cairo-based Arab League called on countries concerned with
the Mideast peace process, particularly the United States, Russia
and members of the European Union, to adopt a serious stance in
the face of Israel's policies that run counter to international
principles.
</P>
<P>
The United States and Russia are the co-sponsors of the peace
process. The Arabs are seeking a more active European role in
pushing forward the Arab-Israeli peace drive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
