<HEADLINE> S. African Deputy President to Visit Tanzania On </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 4 (Xinhua) -- South African Deputy
President Thabo Mbeki is expected in the country tomorrow for a
one-day official visit on the Burundi issue.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki is scheduled to hold talks with President Benjamin Mkapa
at the State House, where Mkapa will brief Mbeki on the current
situation in Burundi, a statement issued here today by the
Ministry of Foreign Affairs and International Co-operation said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides would discuss the decision reached last
Wednesday at the Arusha regionlal summit to impose sanctions
against the military regime of Major Pierre Buyoya in Bujumbura,
the statement added.
</P>
<P>
The talks will also be attended by the two countries' foreign
ministers. 
</P>
