<HEADLINE> French Beekeeper Breaks World Record of Gingerbread </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 4 (Xinhua) -- A French woman beekeeper today
broke her own world record of the biggest gingerbread by cooking a
5.95- meter long and 67-kilogram heavy bread.
</P>
<P>
Beatrice Bouchinet-Cochet put 17 kilograms of honey, 25
kilograms of flour, 20 liters of milk and 13 kilograms of spice in
a six-meter long mould to cook a gingerbread in five hours,
according to organizers of the event in Saint-Aubin-sur-Loire,
central France.
</P>
<P>
The claim has been confirmed by two mayors from neighboring
towns, who are mailing the statistics to the Guineas Records.
</P>
</TEXT>
