<HEADLINE> Arab League Calls on Somali Factions to Reconcile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League today called on
Somali warring factions to transcend tribal rivalries and reach
national reconciliation through dialogue.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the Cairo-based league expressed regret over
the continuation of the Somali crisis following the death of the
powerful faction leader Mohamed Farah Aideed.
</P>
<P>
The 22-member Arab League once again offered to host
negotiations between Somali clans to end the fighting. Somalia is
a member of the league.
</P>
<P>
Aideed died Thursday, nine days after he was wounded during a
battle for a neighborhood in south Mogadishu, the country's
capital city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
