<HEADLINE> Palestinian Official Criticizes Israel's Decision on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Palestinian
Legislative Council Ahmed Korei has termed as very dangerous the
Israeli government's decision to lift a ban on expansion of Jewish
settlements in the Palestinian territories.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Cairo-based Sawt Al Arab (Voice of
Arabs) Radio, Korei said that if settlement activities are resumed
there will be no need for peace negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli settlement policy is unacceptable, he said, warning
that the policy may lead to the renewal of confrontation between
the Israelis and the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli cabinet voted unanimously Friday to lift the
building restrictions on construction in the Jewish settlements in
the West Bank and Gaza Strip.
</P>
<P>
The restrictions were imposed by Israel's late Prime Minister
Yitzhak Rabin four years ago to pave the way for peace
negotiations with the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
In the interview broadcast today, Korei called for a firm Arab
stance to prove that there would be neither peace nor
normalization of relations between Israel and the Arabs if the
Jewish state continues its settlement activities in the
Palestinian land. 
</P>
</TEXT>
