<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 1600 GMT, August 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL -- A South Korean prosecutor today demanded the death
penalty and a 278 million U.S. dollar fine for former President
Chun Doo-hwan charged with mutiny, treason and bribery.
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- French economy continued to recess in the second
quarter of 1996, with a 0.1-percent drop in its Gross National
Product (GNP), according to an official economic indicator
published here today.
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Two white teenagers have been arrested and
charged with arson after the burning of a predominantly black
church in a rural community in Dillon, South Carolina.
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Weekend traffic accidents killed 24 holidaymakers on
their way to beach and mountain destinations, local media reports
said today.
</P>
<P>
BERLIN -- Drug-related crime in Germany rose 82 percent in the
first half of this year, as more addicts turn to crime to pay for
their habit, a German official said today. 
</P>
