self-declared "security zone" in south Lebanon, Israel Radio
reported.
</P>
<P>
One of the soldiers was seriously injured, the other lightly,
when their post in the Bra'shit area in north of the security zone
was under attack by unidentified gunmen.
</P>
<P>
The two wounded soldiers were immediately flown by helicopters
to the Rambam Hospital in Haifa, northwest of Israel, for
treatment.
</P>
<P>
So far, no one has claimed responsibility for the attack.
</P>
<P>
