<HEADLINE> People's Daily Praises Patriotism of Chinese Athletes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 5 (Xinhua) -- It has been more a competition of
psychology, willpower and spirit of the athletes at the 26th
Olympic Games in Atlanta than skills and abilities, says an
editorial to be carried in tomorrow's People's Daily.
</P>
<P>
The achievements of the Chinese athletes in the games, the
newspaper says, has been a victory of their stamina and skills,
and still more an exploration of their courage and qualities.
</P>
<P>
"With their behavior they have demonstrated their lofty ideals,
which place the motherland ahead of anything else," it says.
</P>
<P>
In the past two weeks, Chinese athletes won 16 gold medals, 22
silver, and 12 bronze in the games, and every medal expresses a
touching story of hard work, and every match is a song of
life. The medals embrace one common topic -- patriotism, the
editorial notes.
</P>
<P>
"The grandeur of the courts is part of painful hard work," it
says. "If one wants to reflect the glory of the motherland and the
expectations of the people, with the raising of the national flag,
one should hold firm to winning honor for the country and be ready
to work industriously until that is achieved."
</P>
<P>
"The Olympic Games are eternal, and the spirit of patriotism is
eternal. It is the eternal spirit of patriotism that continues to
make the Olympic games attractive," the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
It is also the patriotism, collectivism and revolutionary
heroism of Chinese athletes that inspire the patriotic enthusiasm
of the Chinese people, either in China or abroad, the editorial
says. 
</P>
