<HEADLINE> Saudis Rated Top Buyers of Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Saudis are the biggest
consumers of gold as they buy 44.5 million pieces of gold and
jewelry annually, costing up to 3 billion U.S. dollars, Saudi
daily Arab News reported today.
</P>
<P>
This means 17 million people of high annual income in the
kingdom purchase 174 tons of gold every year, the largest
individual average of gold purchase in the world. This amounts to
an annual spending of 1,400 U.S. dollars on gold for every buyer.
</P>
<P>
The paper said Saudi Arabia constitutes the major market of
gold and jewelry in the Middle East region, and it has become one
of the major countries in the world dealing in gold.
</P>
<P>
There are 40 major gold factories in the kingdom with an
annual production capacity of one to ten tons. There are also
300 small workshops making jewelry, 50 wholesale gold dealers and
about 3,000 retail shops selling gold and jewelry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
