<HEADLINE> Closer Ties for Shanghai and Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Cooperation and contacts between
China's largest metropolis and Hong Kong have grown dramatically
in recent years.
</P>
<P>
A large picture exhibition, "Hong Kong: History and
Development", was on display today, with the fifth part, "Shanghai
and Hong Kong Join Hands For Coming Century", attracting a lot of
attention.
</P>
<P>
Experts believe that, as July 1, 1997 draws closer and
sovereignty over Hong Kong returns to China, cooperation and
contacts between the two cities will be given greater impetus.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has become Shanghai's largest trade and investment
partner, and bilateral cooperation extends to science, education,
culture, publication, sports, radio and TV.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, Hong Kong had invested in 5,870
projects in Shanghai, putting it in first place in overseas
investment in the city. Bilateral trade has been an annual
increase of over 25 percent.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, more than 84 troupes, with 533 artists, exchanged
visits for traditional Chinese opera, dance, and song
performances. Radio, TV, and film exchanges are also on the rise.
</P>
<P>
The two cities have also jointly sponsored five annual
publishing conferences and by the end of last year had signed 203
copyright agreements for 332 works. 
</P>
</TEXT>
