<HEADLINE> Trade Opportunities Between Pakistan, Central Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Trade opportunities between
Pakistan and Central Asian states are tremendous provided visa
process is simplified, a Pakistani official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a seminar, President of the Islamabad Chamber of
Commerce and Industry (ICCI) Munawar Mughal said that Pakistan
business community should exploit great potential in Central Asian
markets.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Mughal also pointed out that Pakistani traders are
facing some difficulties regarding availability of visa with high
fee.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was organized by the Pakistani Export promotion
Bureau on trade opportunities between Pakistan, Uzbekistan and
Turkmenistan.
</P>
<P>
Iftikhar Ali Malik, Vice President of ICCI said on the occasion
that Pakistan has most favorable balance of trade with Uzbekistan.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan has held a number of commercial exhibitions and has
sent trade delegations to Uzbekistan and Turkmenistan for the
expansion of trade, he added.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the seminar, Ambassador of Turkmenistan to Pakistan
Berdiniyazov Sapar said that the trade and economic potential of
both Turkmenistan and Pakistan can be explored to the maximum
extent.
</P>
<P>
He explained that economic policy of Turkmenistan is based on
free market economy with good trade relations with the world.
</P>
<P>
"Our basic items of export are natural gas, cotton, oil, yarn,
handmade carpets, chemical products, salt, and cement, while our
items of import are machinery and hi-technology," he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that his country signed 518 different international
accords by the end of March 1996 with 33 countries.  
</P>
