<HEADLINE> Geology Tour For Young People In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 5 (Xinhua) -- More than 200 youngsters from
China, Canada, Japan, Spain, the United States and China's Taiwan
Province began a nine-day geology tour today.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the tour is to increase interest in and
knowledge of geology. It is conducted by the Youth Conference of
the 30th International Geological Congress (IGC) and China's Youth
Summer Camp on Geology (YSCG).
</P>
<P>
The Youth Conference opened today in Beijing's Geology
Auditorium. Its participants are 14 boys and girls from 13 to 19
years of age, whose parents are participants of the 30th IGC.
</P>
<P>
China's YSCG, one of the country's best-organized scientific
camps, was first held in 1981 by the Geological Society of China
and the Ministry of Geology and Mineral Resources.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 15 years, 130,000 participants in YSCG have
written 130,000 papers and collected more than 200,000 rock
specimens.
</P>
<P>
The 14 members of IGC's Youth Conference and 200 YSCG campers
will take part in the tour, on which they are scheduled to visit
various sites such as the Geological Science Museum, the Great
Wall, and the Imperial Palace.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Hongren, vice-minister of Geology and Mineral Resources,
said that the tour was organized by IGC's Youth Conference and
China's YSCG and is a pioneering event and will promote friendship
among young people from all over the world who are interested in
geology.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
