<HEADLINE> Iran Starts Construction of Largest Dam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani today inaugurated construction of the country's largest
dam in southwestern province of Chaharmahal-Bakhtiari.
</P>
<P>
The Karoun-4 dam project with an investment of 1,180 billion
rials (about 300 million U.S. dollars) is to provide water for
irrigation, prevent floods and produce 750 megawatts of power.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Energy MinisterBijan Namdar Zanganeh said the dam has a
total capacity of about 2 billion cubic meters and a
30-kilometer-long reservoir.
</P>
<P>
The 207-meter-long dam has a 410-meter crown. It is nine meters
wide at the top and 112.5 meters wide at the foundation.
</P>
<P>
The project has three power generating units, each producing
250 megawatts of power. The dam is scheduled for completion in
2004. 
</P>
</TEXT>
