<HEADLINE> Chelsea Beats Ajax in Umbro Soccer Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 5 (Xinhua) -- English Premier League soccer club
Chelsea snatched the Umbro International soccer Trophy with an
impressive 2-0 win over Dutch champions Ajax at Nottingham
Forest's City Ground on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Roberto di Matteo of Italy paced Chelsea through the first half
with amazing ease after the two superbly taken goals in the
opening 16 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Skipper Dennis Wise put Chelsea 1-0 ahead when he burst from an
unmarked place to blaze home a Di Matteo's perfect cross from the
right in the fifth minute.
</P>
<P>
Romanian wing-back Dan Petrescu made it 2-0 in the 16th minute
when he took a splendid diagonal ball by di Matteo and volleyed it
past Ajax' goalie Edwin van der Sar.
</P>
<P>
In the match-up for the third place, played before the final
between the other two participating clubs, English champion
Manchester United scored three goals in eight late second-half
minutes to beat Premiership rivals and tournament hosts Nottingham
Forest 3-1. 
</P>
