<HEADLINE> Macao Inflation Rate Continues to Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The average inflation rate in Macao
during the first half of the year dropped to 5.5 percent from 8.6
percent by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
show that the inflation rate in Macao has been dropping
continuously from the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
The composite consumer price index reached 164.1 in June, up
0.5 percent from May, mainly due to price rise for housing,
transportation and foodstuff, according to the figures. 
</P>
