<HEADLINE> Portugese Minister in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Portugese Secretary of
State for Foreign Affairs and Cooperation Jose Lamego has said
Portugal hopes to see the peace process in Angola completed by
the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Lamego made the remarks to reporters in Andulo, central Angola
yesterday after meeting President of the National Union for Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA) Jonas Savimbi, Angola's official
news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
It is the Angolans who decide on war or peace and at present
peace prevails in the country that has been torn apart in a
19-year civil war, he said.
</P>
<P>
Lamego said his meeting with Savimbi was beneficial as it
helps him understand UNITA's wishes to stick to the peace process
and its worries.
</P>
<P>
The Portugese government and people and the international
community hope that the Angolan peace process will have been
completed by the end of this year, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Lamego arrived here on Friday to start his four-day working
visit to Angola. During his visit, he donated 17 tons of relief
goods worth 550,000 US Dollars to the Angolan government.
</P>
