<HEADLINE> HK GDP Increases 3.1 percent in 1st Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's gross domestic
product (GDP) increased 3.1 percent in real terms in the first
quarter of 1996 over the same quarter in 1995, according to
official preliminary estimates released today.
</P>
<P>
Among the major GDP components, re-exports registered a
moderate growth of 7.5 percent in real terms, while domestic
exports decreased by 7.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Exports of services continued to be supported by strong growth
in tourism and offshore trading activities. An increase of 14.4
percent in real terms was recorded in the first quarter of 1996
over a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, imports of goods and services increased by 5.2
percent and 7.6 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Along with the release of the preliminary GDP estimates for the
first quarter of this year, GDP estimates for 1994 and 1995 have
been revised. The real growth rate of GDP is revised from 5.5
percent to 5.3 percent for 1994 and from 4.6 percent to 4.7
percent for 1995.  
</P>
</TEXT>
