<HEADLINE> Weekly Prices On China's Materials Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Prices of major production
materials continued to drop in China over the past week.
</P>
<P>
According to the China Materials Information Center of the
Ministry of Internal Trade, prices of 38 types of materials rose
last week over the previous week, while 72 dropped and 64 remained
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Of the 39 steel products monitored by the center, 15 recorded a
rise in price, 20 saw a drop, and four remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The per ton price of nonferrous products continued a slight
downward trend, with copper quoted at 24,591 yuan, down 598 yuan,
and aluminum at 16,122 yuan, a drop of 269 yuan.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, most chemical products, including plastics,
and organic and inorganic products continued to drop in
price. Polypropylene, for example, was down 53 yuan at 8,374 yuan
a ton.  
</P>
</TEXT>
