<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ali Mahdi Frowns on Hussein Aidid's Nomination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, August 5 (Xinhua) -- North Mogadishu faction leader
Ali Mahdi Mohamed today characterized the nomination of Hussein
Mohamed Aidid as the president of Somalia as "stupid, selfish and
provocative." It means the situation in Somalia may deteriorate.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters in his office in north Mogadishu, Ali
Mahdi said he and his ally Osman Hassan Ali Atto may revoke the
unilateral ceasefire they announced after late general Aidid died
in south Mogadishu on August 1, 1996.
</P>
<P>
Ali Mahdi has called on the supporters of late Aidid to
refrain from any kind of violence, saying ''that will only
further devastate the deteriorating humanitarian (situation) in
the country.''
</P>
<P>
Mahdi noted it was the civil war that ended the life of late
general Aidid after he was gunned down and wounded in armed
conflicts in Medina neighborhood.
</P>
<P>
According to Mahdi, all the forces of his faction are put on
high alert immediately after the nomination of Hussein Mohamed
Aidid was officially announced yesterday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
A president for Somalia should come democratically on the will
of the vast majority of the people, Mahdi said, "Presidency of a
country is not a personal property to be inherited by the
children.''
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that his militiamen will not fire until they are
fired upon.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, a spokesman for the faction of Osman Atto
said his faction calls on all Somali people to further respect
the ceasefire that is currently holding in Mogadishu and
elsewhere in the country.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman declined to comment about the nomination of
Hussein Aidid, saying, ''it's no difference from the nomination
of his late father 14 months ago in south Mogadishu.''
</P>
<P>
Hussein Mohamed Aidid was sworn in last night to succeed the
post vacated by his late father, General Aidid.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the radio, Hussein Aidid said he is planning to
put into practice all that is written on the transitional charter
and will destroy what he called "both the internal and external
enemies."
</P>
<P>
Hussein Aidid is currently addressing his supporters in
Mogadishu stadium. Thousands of people are gathering there to
support the new nomination of Hussein Aidid. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
