<HEADLINE> Syrian, Lebanese Presidents Meet in Damascus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Hafez al-Assad
held a meeting at noon today with his Lebanese counterpart Elias
Hrawi as soon as the latter arrived here.
</P>
<P>
Political observers in the Syrian capital believe that the
Syrian and Lebanese presidents are expected to examine the latest
developments of the conditions in the region, including the the
so-called "Lebanon First" proposal put forward by the hardline
Israeli Likud government.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli proposal calls for an unilateral Israeli withdrawal
from south Lebanon in exchange for a disarmament of the Lebanese
pro-Iranian Hezbollah, or the Party of God, and a mechanism to
guarantee the security on the Lebanese-Israeli border.
</P>
<P>
Both Syria and Lebanon have rejected the Israeli proposal out
of the suspicion that the proposal was aimed at driving a wedge
between the Syrian and Lebanese tracks of peace talks with Israel.
</P>
<P>
Syrian President al-Assad will brief Lebanese President Hrawi
on the outcome of the talks he had Saturday with King Hussein of
Jordan on ways of securing Arab solidarity, in addition to the
developments of the Middle East peace process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
