<HEADLINE> HK Media Seminar in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 5 (Xinhua) -- A seminar for members of the Hong
Kong media was held by the Information Office of the State Council
in Beijing between July 29 and August 4.
</P>
<P>
Scholars and officials from State Council departments were
invited to give talks and discuss topics of common interest.
</P>
<P>
Leading officials from relevant departments told the seminar
that the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR) provides a guarantee of press freedom in Hong Kong. After
1997, the SAR government will take charge of Hong Kong's media
operations, and there will be no interference from the inland
areas.
</P>
<P>
They also expressed the belief that media exchanges and
cooperation between Hong Kong and the interior will increase and
that it will be more convenient for Hong Kong journalists to
cover news events in the interior in future.
</P>
<P>
Thhose attending the seminar said that it helped provide a
better understanding of the interior and that they hope there
will be more such seminars in future.
</P>
<P>
Zeng Jianhui, director of the Information Office of the State
Council, Lu Ping, director of the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs
Office of the State Council, and other senior officials met with
members of the media.  
</P>
</TEXT>
