<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Syrian Daily denounces Israel for Expanding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The Syrian newspaper "al-Baath,"
mouthpiece of the ruling party, denounced Israel in its editorial
today for expanding Jewish settlements in the occupied Arab
territories.
</P>
<P>
"Instead of declaring its commitment to the peace process, the
Tel Aviv government makes decisions that are quite far from the
(Middle East) peace process," al-Baath said.
</P>
<P>
"He who does really want and seek a genuine peace has to go
back to the Madrid (Conference) principles and foundations and to
declare he is committed to implementing them," the paper said.
</P>
<P>
"But for Israel it is undoubtedly not intended to achieve a
genuine peace in any way to start a new process of wide-scale
expansion of settlements, to refuse to withdraw from the Golan
(Heights) and the other occupied Arab territories and to consider
Jerusalem it capital for ever. All that interests Israel is to
expand the Jewish settlements at the expense of the Arabs," the
daily added.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli cabinet decided last Friday to end the four-year
ban, imposed by the previous Labor government, on settlement
construction. Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu described
the move as a step to "correct the discrimination against Jewish
settlement" in the occupied Arab territories.
</P>
<P>
Al-Baath said what the Arab citizens need at present is to
adhere to their national and nationalist rights and not to
surrender any of them at all by hammering out a unified Arab stand
to keep the enemy from achieving any of their objectives.
</P>
<P>
The Arabic language daily said Syria would do its best to
establish a fair and overall peace in the region, urging the
hardline Israeli Likud government to abide by the peace process,
and not to insist on its own prejudices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
