<HEADLINE> Thai PM Sues Daily over Bribery Charge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Thai Prime Minister Banharn
Silpa-Archa has filed a lawsuit against the Siam Post over the
daily's allegations that his party had received bribery from a
Swedish submarine builder.
</P>
<P>
The Siam Post published a report late last year, saying the
Swedish submarine builder, Kockums, had given bribe money to some
senior members of Banharn's Chart Thai (Thai Nation) Party in
order to win a contract to sell two submarines to Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Banharn denied the allegations, saying the allegation could
damage his party's image.
</P>
<P>
Banharn said he had never known that submarines would be bought
before the general election on July 2, 1995, according to the Thai
news agency today.
</P>
<P>
However, the agency did not say when the lawsuit was lodged.
</P>
