<HEADLINE> Dalian Becomes Key Fishery Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Dalian, a coastal city in
northeast China's Liaoning Province, has developed into a key
fishery base in northern China.
</P>
<P>
Dalian produced 1.38 million tons of aquatic products last
year, accounting for one tenth of the country's total offshore
catches, and exported 151,000 tons, more than one fifth of the
country's total.
</P>
<P>
At present, the city has 260 aquatic processing plants with an
annual value added totalling three billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
With more than 40 fishing vessels Dalian has set up a number of
fisheries and markets overseas, and has approved 530
foreign-funded enterprises that specialize in fishery.  
</P>
