<HEADLINE> 203 Rebels Killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 5 (Xinhua) -- At least 203 Tamil rebels were
killed and over 100 others injured Sunday in the second phase of
the "Sathjaya" (Certain Victory) operation launched by government
troops in the Northern province of Sri Lanka, a military spokesman
said here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman, Tar Dunuwille, said that government troops
Sunday morning launched the second phase operation, nine days
after the first one. The troops had advanced up to three
kilometers southwards from the strategic town of Paranthan under
the rebels' resistance.
</P>
<P>
During Sunday's action, a government officer and 13 soldiers
were killed while 32 others were wounded, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Sri Lanka's Air Force provided air support to
the advancing troops and assisted in casualty evacuation while the
Navy continued to patrol the Jaffna lagoon to prevent rebel boat
movements, the spokesman added.  
