<HEADLINE> Ningxia Reaps Good Summer Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region, norwest China, reaped 900 million kilograms of summer
grain this year, an increase of 23 percent over 1995.
</P>
<P>
According to the regional agricultural department, the autumn
grain is healthy and growing better than in previous years, and a
good harvest is in sight.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia, where the people of ethnic Hui group live in compact
community, is one of the country's key market-oriented grain
production bases.
</P>
<P>
Since 1985, it has used state investment and funds from the
World Bank and other international organizations to develop
a comprehensive agriculture program.
</P>
<P>
While encouraging local officials to shoulder the
responsibility for grain production, the autonomous region has
increased its input in farming and has spread information on
agro-techniques. 
</P>
