<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guatemalan Government to Hold New Peace Talks With Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The negotiators are scheduled to start today the second round
of discussions about the future political life of the rebel
Guatemalan National Revolutionary Unit (URNG) and the post-war
changes to the army.
</P>
<P>
The two sides met in June, scoring results on such matters as
a civilian minister of defense, reduction and modernization of
the army, and a legitimate role for rebel fighters once they
ended their exile.
</P>
<P>
The government has met with the URNG for sporadic talks over
the last five years. Both sides have signed seven accords on a
list of 11 proposed themes.
</P>
<P>
The process accelerated this year with the signing of major
social and economic agreements and a unilateral ceasefire by the
rebels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
