<HEADLINE> Vietnam  Becomes Member of Regional Shoe Makers Association </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 5 (XINHUA) -- Vietnam has been admitted to the
Asian-Pacific Shoe Makers' Association as an official member,
Vietnam News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The country turned out 152 million pairs of shoes last year, an
increase of 15 percent over the 1994 figure, and is striving to
increase its annual growth rate to between 20 and 25 percent by
the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The growth in the country's shoe production is attributed to
the technological renovation for Vietnam to join the international
market, said the report. 
</P>
