<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Import More Urea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam is planning to import
182,000 tons of urea before mid-August.
</P>
<P>
Local press reported that about 200,000 tons of urea are
currently kept in store nationwide. It is estimated that Vietnam's
minimum requirement for urea before the summer-autumn rice harvest
is about 430,000 tons. However, only 380,000 tons of urea can be
available at home.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam annually needs 1.5 million tons of urea for
agricultural production, of which the country can produce about 9
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
