<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkish Premier to Make First Trip Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Prime Minister Necmettin
Erbakan is expected to pay his first official visit to five
countries in Asia since he came to power.
</P>
<P>
The press office of the prime minister said today that Erbakan
will pay a 10-day visit to Iran, Pakistan, Singapore, Indonesia
and Malaysia, starting from August 10.
</P>
<P>
Erbakan, also chairman of the pro-Islamic Welfare Party (RP),
stressed in his government program that Turkey would further
develop its relations with the Islamic world.
</P>
<P>
Turkish sources said that Erbakan attached great importance to
the strengthening of bilateral relations with neighboring Iran.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Foreign Minister Ali Akbar Velayati said that Erbakan
has always adopted a friendly stance toward Iran and since he is
in favor of having cordial ties with Islamic states, "We are
looking forward to seeing more friendly ties between Iran and
Turkey in future."
</P>
<P>
Velayati made the remarks immediately after the Turkish
coalition government between the RP and True Path Party (DYP) led
by Erbakan won the vote of confidence in the parliament in early
July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
