<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Higher on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
recover grounds lost early last week on the Singapore market, as
the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index gained another 10.23
points to close at 2,146.72 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was thin at 77.6 million units, valued
at 264.45 million Singapore dollars (about 186.23 million US
dollars). Rises overtook falls by 182 to 106, while 282 other
stocks stayed steady.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Land was the most actively traded stock as it
posted a turnover of 4.89 million units. Kemayan Corporation was
next with 3.99 million shares traded, while Berger International
saw 2.88 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Development Bank of Singapore (DBS) Foreign and the
MayBanking shared the top spot on the gainers' list as each of
them picked up by 50 cents to finish at 16.8 and 12.9 Singapore
dollars respectively. The Singapore Land gained 45 cents to close
at 9.55 Singapore dollars, while the Singapore Airlines Foreign
was 40 cents higher at 14.7 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Transmarco was the biggest loser, declining by
40 cents to 9.7 Singapore dollars. FELS lost 25 cents to finish
at 6.65 Singapore dollars and Singmarine fell by 16 cents to 1.83
Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
