<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Crippled People Get Artificial Legs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Ninety percent of legless people in
Vietnam has been given artificial substitutes, local press said
today.
</P>
<P>
Wars have left more than 200,000 disabled people in the country,
80,000 of them need artificial legs.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, international organisations have
provided some 70,000 artificial limbs and hundreds of wheelchairs
for the disabled in Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
They have also offered technology of orthopaedics and technique
in producing artificial substitutes.
</P>
<P>
At present, wooden and aluminium limbs have been replaced by
plastic ones which are lighter, and easier to maintain and cheaper
as well. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
