<DOCNO> XIE19960805.0147 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines' Inflation Rate Further Down in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Measured from a year ago, the
inflation rate in the Philippines further dropped to 8.9 percent
in July from 9.8 percent in June, the National Statistics Office
said today.
</P>
<P>
The office said in a report that on a month-on-month basis,
increases in prices slowed down to 0.1 percent in July, compared
to 0.7 percent in June.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines' inflation had stepped down from nine
consecutive months of two-digit figures only in June as the
economy healed from a rice crisis in September last year.
</P>
<P>
In June, the inflation rate was registered 10.4 percent in the
country. Economic managers are targeting a full year inflation
rate between 7.5 percent and 8.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
On a year-on-year basis, the office said, the inflation rates
in the major commodity groups were on the downtrend except in the
fuel, electricity and water group.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rate was down by 1.6 percentage points in the
food, beverages and tobacco index, 0.9 percentage point in
services, 0.2 percentage point in housing and repairs and 0.1
percentage point in clothing and miscellaneous, the office said.
</P>
<P>
In the fuel, electricity and water group, inflation was up by
0.5 percentage point, it added.
</P>
<P>
The office said that inflation rates in the prices of most of
the major food items, such as rice, corn, fish, fruits and
vegetables, continued to move down in July.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
