<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Maps Charted For Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The State Bureau of Surveying and
Mapping has charted a new map of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region, which will be made public July 1, 1997,
when China resumes the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, the State Bureau of Surveying and Mapping began work
on the map, using three different measurement scales: 1:100,000 (1
cm equals to 1 km), 1:500,000 (1 cm equals to 5 km), and 1:750,000
(1 cm equals to 7.5 km). The map using the scale of 1:100,000 will
be published by the State Council -- China's Cabinet -- during the
period of turnover.
</P>
<P>
The maps of the scales of 1:500,000 and 1:750,000 will be used
as illustrations in newspapers, periodicals, and for educational
materials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
