<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australia Donates Medicine to Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Australia has donated medicines
worth over 10,000 US Dollars to Uganda, English daily "The New
Vision" reported today.
</P>
<P>
TASO (the AIDS support organization) medical liaison officer
in Kampala, Molly Eriki handed over the donation to E. K.
Kakyenkye, chairman of the community initiative at Kashari county
in Mbarala district, some 150 kilometers southwest of here.
</P>
<P>
Eriki said the health center will work as custodians of
the donated drugs and equipment on behalf of the community.
</P>
<P>
The donation will support the TASO community initiative pilot
program in the district whose objectives, among others, are to
decrease HIV transmission through the detection and treatment of
sexually transmitted diseases and to avail people with AIDS with
improved health care. 
</P>
</TEXT>
