<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Exports to Japan Continue to Grow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania should make more
efforts to increase the quantity of its exports to Japan and
improve its quality, a Japanese official said.
</P>
<P>
The Japan Export Trade Organizaton (JETRO) representative to
Tanzania, J. Katamiya said in a statement here recently
that Tanzania should also look afresh into its manufacturing
industry in order to balance its trade with Japan.
</P>
<P>
According to the JETRO statement made available to Xinhua
today, in the three years up to 1994, Tanzania's exports to
Japan grew at an annual rate of 20.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, Tanzania's exports to Japan were worth 64.7 million
US Dollars, compared to 49.3 million US Dollars in 1994, while
Japan sold goods to Tanzania worth 107.7 million US Dollars
during the same period.
</P>
<P>
The statement said Tanzania's exports to Japan
mainly consist of agricultural products like coffee, cloves and
sesame seeds. Other products included fish and beeswax.
</P>
<P>
Among them, coffee is the leading export crop to Japan,
fetching Tanzania 37.8 million US Dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
The increase in coffee exports has been attributed to the rise
in beverage consumption and to price increases of coffee
beans as the frost affected the crop in Brazil, the biggest
coffee producer in the world.
</P>
<P>
The export of sesame seeds fetched 9.1 million US Dollars, a
116 percent increase from 1994 earnings of 4.3 million US
Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The export of fish fillets earned Tanzania 7.7 million US
Dollars last year, which is an increase of 931.1 percent from
1994 earnings.
</P>
<P>
Other products exported to Japan include gemstones and cloves.
Last year, Tanzania fetched a total of 2.1 million US Dollars
from the export of gemstones.
</P>
<P>
The Sale of sisal hemp fetched 473,986 US Dollars making
Tanzania the second highest supplier of the product to Japan.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania is the biggest supplier of beeswax to Japan covering
29.3 percent of the total beeswax imports into Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
