<HEADLINE> Hezbollah Bombard Israeli Position in S. Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Guerrillas of the pro-Iranian
Lebanese Hezbollah, or Party of God, bombarded today a position
of Israeli forces in its self-proclaimed "security zone" in south
Lebanon, causing casualties.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the Islamic Resistance, the military wing of
Hezbollah, announced that its fighters attacked the Israeli
position located between the villages of Beit Yahoun and Barashit
with rocket-propelled grenades (RPG) this morning and "directly
hit the targets."
</P>
<P>
Security sources in south Lebanon reported that more than 10
RPGs fired by the Shiite Moslem guerrillas exploded inside the
Israeli position.
</P>
<P>
Israel Radio confirmed that one Israeli soldier was wounded in
exchange of fire with Lebanese guerrillas in the eastern sector
of the buffer zone this morning.
</P>
<P>
In retaliation for the attack, the Israeli occupation forces
from their positions in the 15-kilometer-wide border strip opened
fire with mortar shells and heavy machine guns at Jibal Rafih in
Iglim Al-Toffah, or Province of Apple, according to the security
sources.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen Israeli soldiers have been killed in sporadic clashes
on the last active battlefront of the Arab-Israeli conflict since
 a U.S.-brokered cease-fire understanding between Lebanon and the
Jewish state last April, which ended a 16-day Israeli blitz in
south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, a five-state cease-fire monitoring
committee on south Lebanon is to hold its first meeting in Cyprus
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Beirut daily An-Nahar said this morning that the committee
is to meet for the first time after France, Israel, Lebanon, Syria
and the United States completed the nomination of their
representatives to the committee.
</P>
<P>
Their first meeting will be limited to discussions on the
group's regulations of work, its missions and the observers to be
sent to south Lebanon, according to the report. 
</P>
