<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops Launch Further Offensives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
launched another major offensive against rebels of the Liberation
Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE), security sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The sources reported "slow but satisfactory" progress of the
new offensive, code-named Sathjaya (Certain Victory) II, nine days
after operation Sathjaya I during which the strategic town of
Parantha was recaptured.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels were putting up tough resistance with mortars,
rocket propelled grenades and small arms but the troops have been
advancing with no casualties so far, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The troops, backed by tanks, artillery and air cover, were
moving deeper into the rebel-controlled area in a bid to seize
Kilinochchi town. The rebels moved their operational headquarters
to the town in April after the military retook Jaffna city.
</P>
<P>
The sources added that during Sathjaya I, the LTTE lost 54
cadres while the military lost 16 men.  
</P>
