<HEADLINE> Hebei Reports Overall Economic Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, August 5 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei Province
has made headway in economic growth this year, with an industrial
output value totalling 126.6 billion yuan in the first six months
of 1996.
</P>
<P>
This figure is up 19.2 percent over the same 1995 period, and
four percent higher than the national average.
</P>
<P>
According to Ye Liansong, Hebei's governor, the province
harvested more than 10 billion kilograms of summer grain this
year, with wheat as its primary crop.
</P>
<P>
The turnover and profits of the rural industrial enterprises in
the first six months of this year increased by 40 percent and 22.7
percent, respectively, over the corresponding period last year.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of 1996, state and other economic sectors
invested 21 billion yuan in fixed assets, up 45.7 percent over the
January-June period in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Ye noted that the province has succeeded in initiating the
modern enterprise system and forming enterprise groups.
</P>
<P>
While cooperating with other provinces and cities to boost the
local economy, Hebei also used 726 million yuan of foreign
investment in the January-June period, up 74.5 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
