<HEADLINE> China Publishes History on Discovery of Mineral Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 5 (Xinhua) -- China is publishing a 29-volume
book series which is believed to be the authoritative historical
record of the country's discovery of mineral deposits.
</P>
<P>
Four volumes of the book, "The Discovery History of Mineral
Deposits in China," have been published.
</P>
<P>
The mineral deposits fall into three categories: unusually
large mineral deposits, or medium-sized and small mineral deposits
with special features in each province or in the country; mineral
deposits with different genetic types; and mineral deposits that
have national and international significance.
</P>
<P>
The series of books are being compiled by the Department of
Geological Exploration and Planning of the Ministry of Geology and
Mineral Resources.  
</P>
</TEXT>
