<HEADLINE> Malaysia Records Trade Surplus in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia registered an
external trade surplus of 238.169 million ringgit (about 95.267
million U.S. dollars) in May this year against a deficit of 253.9
million ringgit (about 101.56 million dollars) in April this year.
</P>
<P>
This turnaround was due to exports rising by 6.4 percent to
16.992 billion ringgit (6.8 billion dollars) compared with imports
totaling 16.753 billion ringgit (6.7 billion dollars), according
to the Statistics Department today.
</P>
<P>
The improved trade performance in the month under review, the
department said in its interim report, slashed the trade deficit
for the first five months of this year to 1.372 billion ringgit
(548.8 million dollars) compared with a deficit of 3.473 billion
ringgit (1.389 billion dollars for the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
In the first five months of this year, exports rose by 8.1
billion ringgit (3.24 billion dollars) or 14.5 percent to 80.273
billion ringgit (32.11 billion dollars) while imports grew by 8.1
billion ringgit (3.24 billion dollars) or 11 percent to 81.646
billion ringgit (163.29 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
Exports during the January-May period 1995 totaled 70.106
billion ringgit (28.042 billion dollars) while imports amounted to
73.58 billion ringgit (29.432 billion dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
