arrested and charged with arson after the burning of a
predominantly black church in a rural community in Dillon, South
Carolina.
</P>
<P>
Dennis Martin Moody Jr. and Neil Talbot, both 17, are accused
of burning the wood-framed Springhill AME church to the ground
Thursday morning, the Associated Press quoted state Law
Enforcement Division spokesman Hugh Munn as saying.
</P>
<P>
Munn said authorities had not yet determined a motive for the
arson attack.
</P>
<P>
The FBI and the Federal Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms
have been assisting local authorities in Dillon, located near the
North Carolina state border.
</P>
<P>
There have been more than 70 suspicious fires at church
properties belonging to predominantly black congregations in
U.S. southern states since 1995. An equal number of fires have
been reported at white churches in the region.
</P>
<P>
There is evidence of racism in at least 18 of the fires, police
say. Racial motivation has been ruled out in more than two dozen
other cases.  
