<HEADLINE> World Bank Gives Thailand Discount on Interest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Thailand has been given a
discount on the interest it must pay this year on its outstanding
World Bank loans, a Thai official said.
</P>
<P>
Thailand is the first country in the world to have been offered
such a privilege, said Director General of the Fiscal Policy
Office Somchai Richuphan.
</P>
<P>
This year, Thailand has to pay the World Bank 133,879 U.S.
dollars in interest but a letter had just been received from the
multilateral lending agency offering a discount of 4,535 dollars,
or 3.38 percent of the total payable interest.
</P>
<P>
The discount was the maximum permissible and indicated the
country has a sound record for the prompt repayment of loans,
Somchai said.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's outstanding borrowings with the World Bank as at the
end of January stood at 1.392 billion dollars.  
</P>
