<HEADLINE> Japan Launches Major Glass Investment in Czech Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Asahi Glass is to invest 7
billion yen (65 million U.S. dollars) to build eastern Europe's
largest flat glass production line in the Czech Republic, news
reports here say.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the plant, said to be Japan's largest
investment in eastern Europe since the end of the Cold War, will
begin by the end of the year in Teplice, a city in the west of the
republic.
</P>
<P>
Production, expected to be around 600 tons a day, will not only
meet domestic demand but will also be exported to other countries
in central and eastern Europe. 
