<HEADLINE> Japan Provides Power Equipment to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, Aug 5 (Xinhua) -- A 120-million-US-dollars equipment
contract was inked over the weekend in Beijing between Chinese and
Japanese companies, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Under the contract, Japan's Mitsubishi Heavy Industries Co Ltd,
Mitsubishi Electric Corp and Mitsubishi Corp are to provide
boilers and turbine-generators for the Baoshan Power Plant in
Shanghai, the English language paper said.
</P>
<P>
The contract is with the International Economic and Trade Corp
of the Baoshan Iron and Steel Group (Baogang) and the China
National Technical Import and Export Corp(CNTIC), it said.
</P>
<P>
CNTIC, China's largest technology trader, has been entrusted by
Baogang, the country's biggest steel conglomerate and the
proprietor of the Baoshan Power Plant, to conduct international
bidding for purchasing the equipment, the paper added.
</P>
<P>
The equipment was purchased by using the third batch of
Japanese governmental loans worth 810 billion yen (about 7.6
billion US dollars), the paper added.
</P>
<P>
The equipment to be provided under the contract is the third
generating unit of the power plant. The first two were also
provided by the Mitsubishi Heavy Industries Co Ltd, in 1979 and
1982, it said.  
</P>
