<DOCNO> XIE19960805.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S.A. Beats Brazil to Win Olympic Women's Basketball Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The United States women's
basketball team brought home the gold medal by a brillent vicotry
of 111-87 in the final on the closing day of the Atlanta Olympic
Games here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Brazil finished with the silver and the bronze medal went to
Australia, a 66-55 winner over Ukraine earlier.
</P>
<P>
Lisa Leslie scored a game high 29 points for the United States
who also grabbed a team high six rebounders. Ruthie Bolton and
Sheryl Swoopes added 15 and 16 for the United States respectively.
</P>
<P>
Brazil was led by Janeth Arcain with 24 points and Sooza sobeal
Marcari Oliva hit 19 and 11 respectively.
</P>
<P>
After tailing 1-0 in the first minute, the Americans jumped
ahead 3-1 on a three pointer by Bolton and never looked back on
the way to a 57-46 lead at the end of the first half.
</P>
<P>
The inspired Americans never slowed down their pace in the
second half and extented the leading margin to 21 points at 10:21
with 76-55.
</P>
<P>
Staley Dawn came from the bench with her magic dribbling skills
which turned the game into a showcase of no-look passes and
Americans fastbreaks. the American players outside the court
started to celebrate their victory when they were 92-62 ahead with
only 5:51 left on the clock.
</P>
<P>
Amerincan head coach Tara VanDerveer rested all her starters in
the final four minutes and let the Brazilians reduce the gap to 24
points.
</P>
<P>
VanDerveer thought it was her team's defense that held off the
attacking of the Brazilian team, which got 16 turnovers and
allowed the U.S. team 12 steals.
</P>
<P>
"Our defense was the key to win. Our defense was good and our
subs were good," said VanDerveer, the only female head coach among
the 12 women's teams.
</P>
<P>
The veteran-paced Brazilian team seemed to be outrun by their
younger rivals. World Championship MVP Hortencia, regarded as one
of the greatest women basketball players, was held to just 11
points in 27 minutes.
</P>
<P>
"Even we lost, we shot the ball really well in the first half,"
said Brazilian head coach Miguel Angelo. "In the second half, we
had a difficult time getting back on defense and this hurt our
games."
</P>
<P>
"I got tired. Our team did what we could. We still scored 87
points," said Hortencia, the oldest women basketball player in
Atlanta at 37.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
