<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Court of Arbitration Reinstates Russian Offenders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Two Russian athletes were
reinstated by the Court of Arbitration for Sport Ruling (CAS) here
Sunday, and would retain their bronze medals stripped early by the
International Olympic Committee (IOC) for drugs.
</P>
<P>
In its statement, CAS reaffirmed its anti-doping fight and
strict liability for doping offenses, but granted Russian athletes
the benefit of the doubt because of insufficient scientific
evidence.
</P>
<P>
CAS Secretary General Jean-Philippe Rochat said his panel
accepted the appeal filed by swimmer Andrei Korneyev and wrestler
Zafar Guliyev on July 29 after being tested positive for
bromantan, and they would get their medals back.
</P>
<P>
Bromantan was a new substance which the IOC Medical Commission
characterized as a stimulant banned under the Medical Code.
</P>
<P>
The athletes appealed to CAS, arguing that the Russian
delegation used this drug to strengthen the athletes' immune
system, especially for a competition held in a hot and humid
climate, not to enhance performance.
</P>
<P>
In addition to hearing the parties, CAS appointed a neutral
scientific expert professor Holbrook of Mercer University,
Atlanta, who gave detailed evidence on the properties of
bromantan.
</P>
<P>
The expert concluded that from the scarce scientific literature
available, bromantan may well be a performance-enhancing
stimulant.  However, he could not rule out the possibility that
it is used for the sole purpose of strengthening the immune
system.
</P>
<P>
On this basis, the CAS panel decided that it was not proven
that bromantan is a stimulant to a standard sufficient to justify
a sanction as severe as the withdrawal of their medals from the
athletes.
</P>
<P>
Accordingly, they granted the athletes the benefit of doubt.
</P>
<P>
However, the panel also urged the Russian Olympic Committee to
discontinue the use of bromantan by Russian athletes as long as
the doubts cast on its properties are not removed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960805.0223 </DOCNO>
