<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Reid Floors Cuban for Olympic Gold Medal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan, Ukraine and Thailand
won their first-ever Olympic boxing gold medals on Sunday when the
boxing tournament ended.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan light heavyweight Vasilii Jirov, who was judged the
winner of the Val Barker Cup for the boxer with the best technique
during the tournament, claimed gold when he outpointed South
Korean Seung-Bae Lee 17-4.
</P>
<P>
Somluck Kamsing dedicated his gold medal -- Thailand's first --
to his king Brumiphol Adouldash on his golden jubilee year, after
getting an 8-5 points featherweight verdict over Bulgarian world
champion Serafim Todoro.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine's Vladimir Klichko ended Wolfgram's fairytale Olympics
with a 7-3 points decision in the super heavyweight.
</P>
<P>
Despite Duvergel's dramatic knockout, the Cubans finished the
leading team at the Olympics with four gold and three silver
medals.
</P>
<P>
However, David Reid's knockout punch of Cuban Alfredo Duvergel
salvaged American pride. An over the top right-hand from Reid with
35 seconds left in his light middleweight final earned the only US
gold medal of the competition, and avoided their first gold
drought since the 1948 London Olympics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
