<HEADLINE> Netherlands Wins Men's Volleyball Gold Medal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- The Netherlands defeated Italy
3-2 to take the gold medal of the Olympic men's volleyball
tournament Sunday after two and a half hour thrilling competition.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands, runners-up at both Olympics and world
championship, used their powerful kills to beat the Italians,
world champion but fifth place finisher at the Barcelona Olympics,
15-12, 9-15, 16-14, 9-15 and 17-16.
</P>
<P>
Van Meulen led the Netherlands with 34 kills while Van Goor
killed 27. Italy's Andrea Giani contributed 36 kills for his team
but made six fouts.
</P>
<P>
Eealier Sunday, Yugoslavia downed Russia 15-8, 7-15, 15-8, 15-9
to take the silver medal. Russia was fourth.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Brazil finished fifth, Cuba sixth, Bulgaria
seventh and Argentina eighth.  
</P>
</TEXT>
