<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Orders Closure of Palestinian Legislator's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Israeli police today ordered a
Palestinian legislator to close his office in east Jerusalem,
saying he violated a ban on Palestinian official activity in the
self-claimed Jewish capital.
</P>
<P>
Public Security Minister Avigdor Kahalani issued the order by
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to Palestinian Council member
Abdel khader, demanding that he close the office at his home by
Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
But the minister declined to elaborate on the measures to be
taken if the deadline misses.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Khader denounced Israel's action as "illegal,"
saying he was not a member of the Palestinian National Authority
(PNA). He said that he would appeal against the order, because
the office provided him an opportunity to serve the voters who
elected him.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu today blasted the PNA for violating the bilateral
agreements preventing PNA's official activity in east Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
"The Palestinian Authority has made a solemn commitment to
prvent the operation of any government activity in the Jewish
state, especially in the capital of the Jewish state...We are
witnessing the violation of that solemn commitment," he said in a
speech, referring to Khader's office.
</P>
<P>
The status of Jerusalem has been one of the major disputes
between Israel and the PNA.
</P>
<P>
Israel has declared Jerusalem as the "eternal and indivisible
capital" of the Jewish state, denying any compromise on its
self-claimed sovereignty over the holy city.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the PNA has insisted east Jerusalem should be the
capital of a future independent Palestinian state and urged
Israel to resolve the issue through the final-status talks.
</P>
<P>
Israel, under the previous dovish Labor-led government, started
the final-status talks with the PNA in early May, but the talks
soon hit a snag mainly due to hard-line Likud party leader
Benjamin Netanyahu won the Israeli May 29 elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
