<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Croatia Beats Sweden to Win Men's Handball (Updated) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, August 4 (Xinhua) -- Croatia defeated Sweden 27-26 in
a clash between two European countries in the gold medal game of
men's handball tournament here today.
</P>
<P>
The victory brought the Croats their first Olympic gold at the
26th Olympic Games, which close this evening.
</P>
<P>
"I am very happy. We wanted the gold from the first day and we
worked to win it," said Velimir Kljaic, head coach of the Croatian
team. "I am not surprised at all."
</P>
<P>
The Swedish opened the score, but missed several goals,
including a penalty shot, in the first minutes. The Croats scored
six consecutive goals to lead 7-6. The Swedes made a surge, but
were only able to cut their deficit to four goals. At the end of
the first half, the Croats scored another goal, finishing 16-11.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, the Croats expanded their lead to 20-13 in
the first 10 minutes. But the Swedes made a late game surge to cut
their deficit to one goal with three minutes to go. The Croats
were within their striking distance.
</P>
<P>
In a tense atmosphere, the two teams traded goals. The Croats
scored a goal to lead 27-25 with 26 seconds left and the Swedes
returned a goal before the end, missing the gold medal by one
goal.
</P>
<P>
"During the whole game, we were the better competitor, leading
by five goals most of the game," Kljaic said. "Our victory was
supposed to be more convincing, but the Swedish goalkeeper at the
end of the game made great blocks, making it a closer game."
</P>
<P>
Han Hansson, team leader of the Swedish team, said, "I think we
lost the match in the first 10 minutes of the game. We scored one,
Croatia scored six."
</P>
<P>
Earlier today in the bronze medal game, Spain beat France 27-25
to win the third place in the men's handball tournament.
</P>
<P>
In the women's tournament, Denmark upset defending champion
South Korea Saturday to capture the gold medal. South Korea,
two-time Olympic champion, received the silver. Hungary took the
bronze after triumphing over Norway in the bronze medal game.
China was the fifth after defeating the United States and Germany.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
